below zero.tips: Good brawlers will have high mobility or ball control.

cool box.tips: Open map but it's very punishing if you get pushed back from agro. Be wary of high mobility brawlers that can easily score goals (counter then with stun/slow). Hit your shots, keep good positioning, and catch enemies making mistakes.

super center.tips: Tanks better here compared to other Brawl Hockey maps. Lots of good brawlers to go, so identify what tricks a brawler can use to score and adjust to counter or utilize that. Generally, your team composition should have someone good at scoring and someone good at defending.

belles rock.tips: Thrower/Gene/Gray in the middle to pinch throwers. Snipers or high pressure brawlers in the lanes.

out in the open.tips: Sniper heavy draft. Very punishing if you get pushed back so go for at least one tankier brawler to not immediately fall back.

pinball dreams.tips: Get a brawler in the middle, then a tank counter in case of late pick tank, then your own tank.

double swoosh.tips: Be careful about which brawler you select as gem carrier as they can easily get pushed back and countered by enemy gem carrier. Put your antitank to secure grass on the left lane.

center stage.tips: Scouting is important here compared to other Brawl Ball maps. Notable brawlers: Carl, Lumi, Chester, Janet, Poco, Ollie, Lou, Stu, Mr. P, Buster, Melodie, Sandy, Nita.

dueling beetles.tips: Very control based gamemode due to Berry nerf indirectly affecting tanks. Make sure you have someone with decent health to sit on zone.

sneaky fields.tips: Push into the middle grass and force the opponents all the way back to score. Brawlers in the middle to scout/support are good but not as early picks due to enemy being able to push back with tanks.

hard rock mine.tips: Always have control and a tank or tank counter. Balanced team composition makes it so you just have to pick a favorable lane for you. Focus on making space for gem carrier to pick up gems.

parallel plays.tips: Map requires good team synergy. Usually have an anti tank or thrower on left, midrange brawler in the middle to help pinch, and agro on the right.

open business.tips: Control brawlers are really strong, however they are more susceptible to tanks compared to other maps. Make sure you have someone to sit on zone, beware Hank, Draco, Mortis last picks.

flaring phoenix.tips: Thrower/sniper down the left and two others down the middle grass. Don't let someone sneak onto your right side, look out for or ban Kit + Darryl. Comps should usually have a sniper, some sort of mid or long range hybrid, and then a thrower or tank.

undermine.tips: Very hard to win back lane after dying unless your mid helps you pinch. Lots of health or range is important for lane brawlers.

dry season.tips: Make sure you have some sort of wallbreak, agro, or a thrower.

hideout.tips: Snipers are overrated since they get pushed back easily. Spen still likes them and bans Nani as a counter pick against them.

layer cake.tips: Too many walls for snipers compared to other Bounty maps. Even with team last pick don't go brawlers who will get run down in slots 2 and 3.

shooting star.tips: Gray is a centralizing middle lane brawler, ban him and lock down snipers for other lanes.

triple dribble.tips: Best thrower map, however tanks are too aggressive this meta.

starr garden.tips: More walls to peak shots compared to other Brawl Hockey maps. Lots of single shot brawlers are good here (off meta spawner counters). Look out for agro strategies by picking an antitank.

gem fort.tips: Messy map, easy for enemy to last second steal all your gems. Have brawlers good at scouting or able to break grass to have a relative idea of where enemies are. Be sure to consider where enemies for your teammates' lanes are to avoid getting sneaked up on.

ring of fire.tips: Have a brawler in the middle to contest zone, another brawler to move into enemy grass, and other enemy to assist mid or prevent enemy from sneaking into grass. Note: Bo is around Lou tier in the graphic.

new horizons.tips: You must get the right lane matchups to win. Always have at least one wall break option, as that can allow the game to favor throwers or tanks more.
